x_naci_survey_partnership_program_survey.advisory_specify: Not sure what this means but I'm not aware of any "follow-up actions". We worked with DEA to publish two PARs from one SPL approved concept. We were not told that advisory council clearance was necessary.

“Only PAs and PARs, never RFAs, have been published without obtaining Concept clearance at an open session of an advisory council. Until now, Concepts for PAs and PARs have only required approval by NCI's Scientific Program Leadership and the NCI Director. From now forward, all Concepts, including those for PAs, PARs, and RFAs, will also be reviewed and need to be approved by the NCI's Board of Scientific Advisors (BSA) before the corresponding/resulting funding opportunity announcements (FOAs) can be released to the public by publication in the NIH Guide for Grants and Contracts.”

x_naci_survey_partnership_program_survey.renewal_specify: Often pvt sector partners who have participated in partnerships are asked by FNIH to support an extension/or enlargement of the project based on scientific findings/data obtained from the initial partnership agreement.

x_naci_survey_partnership_program_survey.renewal_specify: We have had previous partnerships with the USDA and the current partnership has evolved into a partnership with its foundation which is lead by Dr. Sally Rocky, previously of the NIH.
